                        <extent>231 folios 
									
								</extent>
                        <collation>
                           <p>
									24 quires: ithree (folios 1-3), ii-xi10 (folios 4-103), xii10 (folios 104-105, 105a-112), xiii-xxi10 (folios 113-202), xxii10 (folios 203-208, 208a-211), xxiii-xxiv10 (folios 212-231). 
									Catchwords at the end of the quires, sometimes decorated.
								</p>
                        </collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 38;
                                                  written lines: 38; Uniform layout.Visible hard-point ruling.Initial words written in larger characters.Hair side and flesh side are indistinguishable.Erasures presumably by the censor (e. g. folios 15r, 116v, 224v, 227r).
Unfoliated blank leaf after folios 105, 208.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
